  "description": "Solanaceae herb from tropical and subtropical Asia. Domesticated from Solanum insanum (wild progenitor, South/Southeast Asia). Produces large berries with dark purple, white, striped, or green skin; white spongy mesocarp. Multiple domestication events in Asia created Occidental (Mediterranean) and Oriental (Southeast Asian) morphotypes. Protogynous buzz-pollinated flowers.",
  "name": "Solanum melongena",
